args: Sorry for the delay, everybody—but your\ntrusty maid Melody is finally done with\nher outfit swap. Ta-daaaaaah!
And in these sweet new threads,\nI'm ready to get out there and\ngrab Valentine's BY THE THROAT!
Which means it's time for me to hop in\nthe kitchen trenches and help everybody\nwhip up some tasty treats.
She, uh, seems rather excited considering\nshe only changed because she spilled\nchocolate all over her last outfit.

Ah, but I can understand her eagerness;
I rarely have the luxury to take time
preparing treats, and I find myself
rather excited at the prospect.
Yeah, but you're normal. In HER case,\nthe moment she gets excited about\nsomething, it causes...issues.
I got the eggs and butter and—AAAAH!
The more eager she is for something,\nthe more furious her fall, it seems.
Aw, boo! I broke the eggs...
That's 'cause you were tearing through\nthe kitchen like your pants were on fire.\n*sigh* Look, can you stand?
Owwww! What is your DEAL, man?!\nI just helped you up, and you toppled\nright back down again—on ME!
I'm sorry! The floor is all super\nslippery for some reason!
THAT'S BECAUSE IT'S COVERED\nWITH BROKEN EGGS!
I beg your pardon, ladies, but you might\nwish to spare a glance behind you.
AAAAAAH! THE STOVE IS ON FIRE!
Ack! Okay, lemme just... Oh noooo!\nI can't put it out! There's a bunch of oil\nor something on the stove!
Did you not come in here carrying\na large amount of butter, Melody?
Actually, yeah. I did. I wonder where\nit all went? I had it, then I dropped the\neggs, sooooo theeeeen...

I believe the butter is currently on fire.
I would suggest rectifying this situation
with all possible speed, lest we burn
down the entire Halidom.
Not to worry! Cleo showed me how to\ndeal with burning oil once!
First, I need a wet towel...\nAh, there we go!
Melody, look out! Your sleeve is\ncaught on that container of—
Fire and dust...\nMy, but that's a bad combination...
EVERYBODY RUN!\nGET OUT OF THE KITCHEN!
How many times do you plan to engulf\nmy kitchen in flames until you have\nsatisfaction, Melody?
I'm really sorry, Cleo. It was an accident.
*sigh* I should have fired you\nwhen I had the chance.

Well, there's nothing for it: Since you
cause nothing but trouble for others,
I hereby ban you from the kitchen
for the duration of Valentine's.
Wait, so I'm a kitchen exile? Noooo!
Still, I suppose this is better than the axe.\nBy which I mean fired, although Cleo\nlooked mad enough to use a REAL axe...
Well, I'll just have to find another way\nto make myself useful.
Oh, I know! I'll clean everyone's rooms!
Oh, hello there, Melody.\nDoing some room cleaning?

Yes indeed, master! Er, but if I can pry,
what are you still doing in your room?
You're usually off fighting fiends or the
like at this hour of the day, right?
I had some things to take care of.\nOh, that reminds me!
Do you happen to know if there's\na good jeweler in the area?
There are a few in one of the nearby\nvillages. Er, do you need one?
I do. See, there's a particular noble family\nthat I'm rather indebted to, and their\ndaughter is coming of age soon.

I wanted to send them a nice gift for the
occasion, and I've been wracking my brain
to figure out something appropriate.
I thought maybe jewelry would work?
Do you want me to come with you to help\npick out something she might like?
That would be great, actually.\nAre you sure you don't mind?
Of course not! It's my job to be\nof service to you in every way!
In that case, it's a deal. I'll head over\nthere in a couple of days, if that works.
Thank you again, Melody. It will be really\nreassuring to have you with me.
Reassuring? Really? Wow, that's the first\ntime in my maid life that anyone's ever\nsaid that about me.

And since he's being so nice, I need to
find a way to show him how much I
appreciate HIM! I mean, what with it
being Valentine's and all.
Okay, but how? I can't just walk up and\nthank him—that would be SUPER dull.
If yer lookin' what to impress the boss\nfor Valentine's, ya can't go wrong with\nwith a heartfelt present.
A present... That's a fine idea, Ranzal!

Yeah, I'm full of 'em. Oh, and after ya give
him the goods, the two of ya can hit a cafe
for tea and some'a them little sandwiches
what with the crusts cut off.
Oh, this just gets better! That would\nhelp him relax from all his daily... Um...
Wait, how long have you\nbeen standing there?
Bwa ha ha! Oh, not that long. Just can't\nhelp but pipe up when I hear folks\nmonologuin' like ya was.

Still, I never thought YOU'D fall for
the boss, too! So what's the plan?
Gonna lay yer feelings out in the open,
or is this more of a stealth deal?
What? N-no! You have this all wrong!\nI mean, of course I like my master,\nbut I don't LIKE like him!

Ain't no need to be shy with ol' Ranzal!
C'mon, spill the dirt. These big shoulders
of mine are great for cryin' on—or we
can just plan yer little date!
Melody and the boss, kissin' in a tree!\nK-I-S-S...uh...S-E...W...?\nAh, hell. I can't spell for crap.
STOP IT, RANZAL! This is just a little\nthank-you—NOT a date!
I mean, sure, it's just the two of us alone\non Valentine's, but that doesn't...mean...
ACK! Wait, IS this a date?!
